Replace the truncated error message in `AdapterCard.tsx` with a Radix Collapsible component that allows users to expand and read the full error text. This is a WCAG-compliant solution using Radix's built-in `aria-expanded`/`aria-controls` management.

## Prerequisites

Install the shadcn Collapsible component:
```bash
npx shadcn@latest add collapsible
```

This will create `apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/collapsible.tsx`.

## Implementation Steps

### Step 1: Install shadcn Collapsible

Run `npx shadcn@latest add collapsible` from the `apps/client` directory. Verify the file is created at `apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/collapsible.tsx`.

Add the export to the shared UI barrel file (`apps/client/src/layers/shared/ui/index.ts`) if it wasn't auto-added:
```typescript
